        <section ids="introduction" names="introduction">
            <title>Introduction</title>
            <paragraph>Horizon is the canonical implementation of <reference name="OpenStack's Dashboard" refuri="https://github.com/openstack/horizon">OpenStack’s Dashboard</reference><target ids="openstack-s-dashboard" names="openstack's\ dashboard" refuri="https://github.com/openstack/horizon"></target>, which provides a web based user
                interface to OpenStack services including Nova, Swift, Keystone, etc.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>For a more in-depth look at Horizon and its architecture, see the
                <reference internal="True" refuri="contributor/intro#contributor-intro"><inline classes="std std-ref">Horizon Basics</inline></reference>.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>To learn what you need to know to get going, see the <reference internal="True" refuri="contributor/quickstart#quickstart"><inline classes="std std-ref">Quickstart</inline></reference>.</paragraph>
